Kicking off 9 days of 9 build_values:

build_values 1/9:

Compassion > Intellect

Compassion is the prerequisite to organic collaboration.  Be humble with intellect and domain knowledge.  Individual expertise is one piece of a larger puzzle.

build_values 2/9

Create > Consume

Seek to create value for others and society where and when you are able; a long-tail of benefits will surely follow for yourself and the community.

build_values 3/9

IRL > URL 

As wonderful as the internet is, it will never replicate the shared memories, serendipity, and impact to society that only in-person interactions can provide.  Be intentional with IRL engagement.

build_values 4/9

Complementary > Exclusionary

All of an individual's attributes and skill sets are complementary to other individual‚Äôs attributes in the build_community.  We cannot assess fish by their ability to climb trees.

build_values 5/9

Scarcity = Innovation 

Resource constraints breed innovation.  Groundbreaking work is often done by small teams with few resources.

build_values 6/9

Actions = Ideas

Ideas inspire action and action refines our ideas.  Both are equal parts necessary to increase the velocity of feedback loops.  Ship early and often.

build_values 7/9

Dignity + Opportunity  

Dignity and opportunity are fundamental rights of all build_members, we actively seek to amplify both for each other rather than impede.

build_values 8/9

Bridges > Ladders

Strong networks are built laterally, not vertically.

build_values 9/9

Contribute > Criticize

Constructive conversations are the path towards breakthrough ideas. Don't subtract without adding, especially when criticizing.
Vision manifests in increments.

Qurrent, based out of our blueprint ecosystem in Coeur d'Alene, Idaho, is building the archetype of electric and intelligent boating.
 https://i.imgur.com/oBalmsp.png

Not only does "Frank", the first prototype, have over 800 HP of electric power in its 33' pontoon hull, but also comes with over 30 sensors and an AI assistant that takes control of the boat when you don't want to.
 https://i.imgur.com/BNfmOHE.jpg

Dubbed "Mariana", the AI assistant operates from the 3D world built by Qurrent's advanced sensors. Mariana can not only see anything and everything around the boat but is also able to map it all providing the database of objects above, below, and on the surface of the water. https://i.imgur.com/BcAV7HB.png

Ingesting all of this data is an array of cutting-edge sensors designed to create a 3D environment that Mariana uses to safely navigate open waters, dock at complex marinas, or even launch and load the boat at the ramp.
 https://i.imgur.com/QrmnoVu.jpg

All this amounts to a boat that can anchor itself, drop passengers off at shore and come back to pick them up, auto-navigate across a body of water (FAST!), and even auto dock and launch itself from the harbor.
 https://i.imgur.com/Wowcl8b.jpg
In a world seemingly dominated today by bits, Qurrent is just one of many examples of a new horizon being built in atoms.
